Class StructuredArrayWithLongIndex<T>

java.lang.Iterable<T>
public final class StructuredArrayWithLongIndex<T>
extends java.lang.Object

An array of objects with semantics restructed to those consistent with layouts of an array of structures in C-like languages. The length and indexes of this array are 64 bit signed longs.

A JVM may optimise the implementation with intrinsics to provide a compact contiguous layout that facilitates consistent stride based memory access and dead-reckoning (as opposed to de-referenced) access to elements
